threads.message:

The board has a green light on the charger and it does charge the battery when the battery is not full but starting ( NO fan spin no video no 5v on s5 rail)[/COLOR][/FONT]

[COLOR=#000000][FONT=verdana]PPbus_g3h 12v
pp342, 3.42[/FONT][/COLOR]

thank you [/FONT][/COLOR]

threads.title: 820-2915-b Not powering up
threads.message: Disconnect airport first of course. Are you using a real 85W charger? You can also let the battery charge up to a few lights on the indicator. Disconnect keyboard and power on the board by shorting C5710 once the battery has some charge.

threads.title: 820-2915-b Not powering up
threads.message:
Yes original power supply nothing connected to the board and battery fully charged
